import React, { useEffect } from "react"; import { useDispatch, useSelector } from "react-redux"; import { StoreData } from "../Redux/Action/action"; const Products = () => { const dispatch = useDispatch(); useEffect(() => { fetch("http://localhost:3000/productdata") .then((res) => res.json()) .then((res) => dispatch(StoreData(res))) .catch((err) => console.log(err)); }, []); const x = useSelector((state) => state.reducer.data); console.log(x); return (
{x.map((e) => { return (

{e.name}

{e.Brand}

{e.category}

{e.price}

{e.Rating}

); })}
); }; export { Products };
